<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
@accepts(gdouble)
@returns(none)
def set_resolution(dpi)
</code></synopsis>
<p>Sets the resolution for font handling on the screen. This is a
scale factor between points specified in a <link xref="PangoFontDescription">PangoFontDescription</link>
and cairo units. The default value is 96, meaning that a 10 point
font will be 13 units high. (10 * 96. / 72. = 13.3).</p><p>Applications should never need to call this function.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>dpi :</p></td>
<td><p>the resolution in "dots per inch" (Physical inches aren't actually involved; the terminology is conventional).</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 0.4</p>
